{
  "stem": "1733.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 192.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They are of Jewish faith.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And these people-- and the German government is going to be responsible for them, to-- to bring them back, so forth and so on.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, it was a formality.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Those-- those orders were worked in the office.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I, working in the office, I was helping with the papers, with the list of-- of the-- the list of prisoners that we're going to be turned over to the German government.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't realize-- we didn't realize how bad it is until we got into the German border.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Because, on the Hungarian side, they were still feeding us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were still housed properly.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The next day, when they turned us over, over the border, when they brought us over the border, and at the train station the-- it was snowing.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was very cold.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Somehow, from sunshine in Hungary, it went into-- to freezing weather into Germany.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The SS were youngsters.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were-- they were young, like young kids, 13-, 14-year-old kids with uniforms.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they saw what was-- what the SS were doing to us, they were standing with tears in their eyes.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I mean, they-- they couldn't comprehend what is happening.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And at-- at that time, they put us on trains.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the train had compartments, two benches on each side, a door leading into the compartment, with a riser on the front of the train.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I think there were 10 of us, in each side, on each bench, sitting in a compartment, about 20 of us in 1 compartment.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The doors were closed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Somehow, we were all hungry and thirsty.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "One of the-- one of our-- one of the guys in the compartment pushed down the window to get some snow to quench his thirst.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
